their driver's test and
you can say to them,

112
00:04:32,017 --> 00:04:34,720
"Hey, I'm sure your test will go well."

113
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:39,270
So a fifth way to respond is
to simply assure the person

114
00:04:39,270 --> 00:04:42,630
that you think everything
will go really, really well,

115
00:04:42,630 --> 00:04:44,520
whatever it is that they're doing.

116
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:46,227
So again, if I said to you,

117
00:04:46,227 --> 00:04:48,980
"Whoa, it's the first day
of school, wish me luck."

118
00:04:48,980 --> 00:04:50,407
You could respond by saying,

119
00:04:50,407 --> 00:04:52,617
"I'm sure you'll have a great day, Bob."

120
00:04:52,617 --> 00:04:54,537
"I'm sure you'll do a good job."

121
00:04:54,537 --> 00:04:58,080
"I'm sure the school day will be awesome."

122
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,440
And of course, lastly,

123
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:01,500
you can always combine a whole bunch

124
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:03,100
of these phrases together.

125
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:05,690
And in fact, English
speakers often do that.

126
00:05:05,690 --> 00:05:07,820
If I was to say to you wish me luck,

127
00:05:07,820 --> 00:05:09,487
you could respond by saying,

128
00:05:09,487 --> 00:05:12,137
"good luck, I hope you have a good day."

129
00:05:12,137 --> 00:05:14,097
"I hope your day goes well."

130
00:05:14,097 --> 00:05:17,817
"I'm sure you'll do a good
job teaching your classes."

131
00:05:17,817 --> 00:05:19,087
"Best of luck."

132
00:05:19,087 --> 00:05:19,937
"All the best."

133
00:05:19,937 --> 00:05:22,190
"I'm sure it will be great."

134
00:05:22,190 --> 00:05:23,830
So again, you don't have to combine

135
00:05:23,830 --> 00:05:25,340
that many of them together,

136
00:05:25,340 --> 00:05:27,870
but when you are responding
to that statement,

137
